caption: In-person dining is now open.  We have lived within two blocks for the last six years and never managed to get there, in spite of recommendations from a number of friends.  We went the other night and absolutely loved it.  The carbonara was particularly good, and the saltimbocca was outstanding.  I lived in Europe for many years and have spent a good deal of time in Italy and this is the real deal, similar to what I've had there.

Love this restaurant! Service is phenomenal. Food is excellent. Highly recommend!

Ate here for a business lunch. The restaurant seems very up scale for a small place down town. Wait staff was quick, efficient, and stealthy. Never noticed A glass of water every being refilled.  To start, the meal began with bread and a small charcuterie plate. The bread was warm and pulled apart easily. The plate was a serving of soppressata, slightly fried green chili, and cubes of parmigiano-reggiano, paired with a sauce cup of oil soaked olives. The peppers provided a delicious kick for the rest of the meal.  T-Bone steak was ordered as the main course. Well cooked, juicy from tooth to fork. No additional seasoning was required. There's a suggestion of dry ageing in the flavor, and USDA prime beef in the texture. The quality of the steak took me off guard, as small restaurants out this much effort into steak unless it's the final point of the business (steak stand chop houses).  Guardino D'oro is a great place fo business lunches overall.
Very tasty food and extremely kind staff. The ambience was perfect and made the experience even better. Make sure to try the cannoli!!

did appreciate the little salami and cheese plate with the bread, and service was 5*. food was good though not spectacular, portions were on the smaller side of reasonable - the intent is probably that you have pasta AND another course for dinner, true Italian style, but just pasta is an ok size for a lunch. but this is NOT $$ range, and even in $$$, it's a bit ridiculous for a plate of pasta primavera and a soft drink (including tax and tip) to cost $45 - especially at lunch. won't be eating here again unless someone else is paying.

Long time downtown Italian restaurant with very high quality foods presented well, without fanfare, by well trained and long experienced staff. They all know the menu and specials 100%, which is very helpful, especially with picky eaters or those with allergies. Not the most diverse of menues, nor most diversified of the many choices for Italian in downtown NYC, but a good assortment. One of the best places within 10 blocks of it's location for either an unexpected, non reserved table, or as pricing for a group of 10 or more. They have comfortable and attractive pricing for groups, although go over the wine separately, as they are in need of pricing adjustment when you're ordering more than one bottle. Same on bottled waters, they will work with you on pricing for small or large groups. Service is excellent. Comfort high. Quality high. Replace a few items on the menu, maybe a add a few for diversity, and buy some different wine selections in mid-price ranges, and  a 5 is in the near future. A solid 4.5 now.

Btw, this open entree does not appear on their menu. We can call this very bad custom: stealing a client.

Any meal at Giardino D'Oro is a perfect one.  Over the years, I've had a chance to taste quite a bit of their dishes and I can say that whether it's a traditional dish or a unique special, these guys always prepare a perfect meal.  The service is impeccable, and the environment is friendly and comfortable.  They cook an amazing steak here too, so if you're in the mood for a delicious piece of steak, look no further.  That's what makes them so interesting:  where else can you get a perfect Italian meal, a perfect steak, or a little of each?  Finish the meal off with a cannoli and you are in heaven.

Giardino D'Oro is more of a downtown Wall street type men-heavy dining spot. My supervisor took me here for a fancy lunch. The entry way is shabby for some reason but the inside decor is far away from shabiness. It has dim lighting and tons of wait staff ready to serve. Each table is provided with a nice free appetizer of cheese, salami and warm bread basket.  I chose their Carbonara pasta for my lunch. It is nicely cooked. Pasta is cooked just right with the right texture and the heavy cream is not overwhelming.  I do reckon this is not a casual dining spot as you would feel slightly under-dressed. Yet. this is definitely a good place to bring clients or treat your employees.

Good food, and pleasingly hard to find -- makes you feel like you've found something off the beaten track. Service is both warm and professional. I recommend dinner over lunch, the lunch crowd is more Wall Street and doesn't know how to relax and enjoy, which lowers the tone of the experience.
